# Research Design

## Paradigm Choice
Simulation / Controlled / Real-world dataset / User study / Theoretical / DSR

## Variables
- Independent (you manipulate)
- Dependent (you measure)
- Controlled (you fix)
- Confounding (mitigate)

## Baselines Rule
One per major SOTA paradigm. Must have public code. Same compute budget.

## Metrics
- Primary (1): directly measures RQ claim
- Secondary (2-4): context
- Accuracy = (TP+TN) / (TP+TN+FP+FN)
- ≥5 seeds, report mean ± std, Wilcoxon test

## Ablation
Remove each component → quantify contribution

## Reproducibility
Fixed seeds + config file + scripted preprocessing + environment file
